    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Historicist architecture style developed around 1910. Reverts to the formal language of architecture of the mid-18th century, from the Louis XV period (1723-1750). Characterised by specific Rococo ornamentation such as irregular shell shapes, rocailles, and a predilection for asymmetry.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
